Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specifyLockupElement(25.10)                        specifyLockupElement(25.10)

Name
       specifyLockupElement - Specifies a cell or instance as a lockup element

Syntax
       specifyLockupElement

       {-cell <leafCellName> | -inst <instName>}

       -in <ftname>

       -out <ftname>

       Specifies  a  cell or instance as a lockup element. Lockup elements are
       present in scan chains where the chain crosses  between  two  different
       clock  domains  or  clock phases. Use this command after running place-
       ment.

Parameters
       -cell <leafCellName>
              Specifies the cell to be a lockup element.

       -in <ftname>
              Specifies the name of the scan input.

       -inst <instName>
              Specifies the instance to be a lockup element.

       -out <ftname>
              Specifies the name of the scan output.

Example
       The following command specifies that cell TLATX1 is  a  lockup  element
       with a scan input pin D and an output pin Q:

       specifyLockupElement -cell TLATX1 -in D -out Q

